#
# .lesskey: input file to lesskey.
# usage: run lesskey to set up special keys for "less".
# Blank lines and lines which start with a pound sign (#) are ignored.
#
x      quit
X      quit
\e[C   next-file
\e[D   prev-file
\eOC   next-file
\eOD   prev-file
#
# By default, \e[ is left-scroll. However, the inclusion of \e[C above
# seems to have disabled \e[ (sort of understandable). So I add \e< as
# a synonym for left-scroll and \e> as a synonym for right-scroll.
\e<    left-scroll
\e>    right-scroll
#
# N = go to next file
# backspace, delete go back one screen.
#
N      next-file
\b     back-screen
\kx    back-screen
